ciscoVismRsrcPartMIB.name: ciscoVismRsrcPartMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of the MIB. The content of this MIB was originally available in SMIv1 version. The MIB has been converted to SMIv2 version and descriptions of some of the objects have been modified.

ciscoVismRsrcPartMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-wanatm@cisco.com
ciscoVismRsrcPartMIB.description: The MIB module containing Port Resource Partition information for VISM service module.

vismPortResPartCnfGrpTable.name: vismPortResPartCnfGrpTable
vismPortResPartCnfGrpTable.description: The vismPortResPartCnfGrpTable contains the configuration of port resource partition. Currently this table contains a single row.

vismPortResPartCnfGrpEntry.name: vismPortResPartCnfGrpEntry
vismPortResPartCnfGrpEntry.description: An entry for port resource partition.

vismResPartPortNum.name: vismResPartPortNum
vismResPartPortNum.description: This is the index to vismPortResPartCnfGrpTable. If PXM1(Processor Switch Module) is used on the shelf this object should be set to 1. For PXM1E this object should be set to 255.

vismResPartRowStatus.name: vismResPartRowStatus
vismResPartRowStatus.description: This will 'add', 'delete' or 'modify' the partition. To delete an entry, this object has to be set to 'del'. The resource partition can be deleted only after deleting all the connections Logical Channel Numbers(LCNs).

vismResPartNumOfLcnAvail.name: vismResPartNumOfLcnAvail
vismResPartNumOfLcnAvail.description: This represents number of LCNs available for this controller and this port. The default value for this object is chosen based on the object vismMode (defined in CISCO-VISM-MODULE-MIB MIB) :

vismResPartLcnLow.name: vismResPartLcnLow
vismResPartLcnLow.description: This represents low end of reserved LCN. The LCN identifies the local VCI(Virtual Channel Identifier) value on the VISM when adding a connection.

vismResPartLcnHigh.name: vismResPartLcnHigh
vismResPartLcnHigh.description: This represents high end of reserved LCN. The LCN identifies the local VCI value on the VISM when adding a connection.

vismResPartIngrPctBW.name: vismResPartIngrPctBW
vismResPartIngrPctBW.description: The percentage of total ingress bandwidth reserved. Since we have only one LCN for VoIP(Voice Over IP), the value is 100.

vismResPartEgrPctBW.name: vismResPartEgrPctBW
vismResPartEgrPctBW.description: The percentage of total egress bandwidth reserved Since we have only one LCN for VoIP, the value is 100.

vismResPartCtrlrID.name: vismResPartCtrlrID
vismResPartCtrlrID.description: This is the controller identifier of the PNNI (Private Network to Network Interface) controller.

ciscoVismRsrcPartCompliance.name: ciscoVismRsrcPartCompliance
ciscoVismRsrcPartCompliance.description: The compliance statement for objects related to VISM Port Resource Partition configuration.

ciscoVismRsrcPartGroup.name: ciscoVismRsrcPartGroup
ciscoVismRsrcPartGroup.description: The collection of objects which are used to represent VISM Port Resource Partition configuration.
